Function

f1 <- function(x) {
  result <- x^2 + 2
  return(result)
}

f2 <- function(x, y) {
  result <- x^2 + y^2 - 4
  return(result)
}

f <- function(x, y) {
  result <- x + (2 * y) + 3
  return(result)
}

#create dataset
Student <- c("John ncuti", "Angela bakame", "Bruce wizeye", "Alexis aganze", 
             "claude Rukundo", "Joel Kagabo", "Mary ineza")
Math <- c(600, 412, 358, 495, 512, 410, 522)
Science <- c(95, 99, 80, 82, 75, 89, 77)
English <- c(25, 22, 18, 20, 29, 30, 27)

roster <- data.frame(Student, Math, Science, English, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

str(roster)
## 'data.frame':    7 obs. of  4 variables:
##  $ Student: chr  "John ncuti" "Angela bakame" "Bruce wizeye" "Alexis aganze" ...
##  $ Math   : num  600 412 358 495 512 410 522
##  $ Science: num  95 99 80 82 75 89 77
##  $ English: num  25 22 18 20 29 30 27
z<-scale(roster[,2:4])
score<-apply(z,1,mean)
roster<-cbind(roster,score)
y<-quantile(score,c(.8,.6,.4,.2))
## create a grade variable us
roster$grade[score>=y[1]]<-"A"
roster$grade[score<y[1]&score>=y[2]]<-"B"
roster$grade[score<y[2]& score>=y[3]]<-"C"
roster$grade[score<y[3]& score>=y[4]]<-"D"
roster$grade[score<y[4]]<-"F"
#### Dealing with names
name<-strsplit((roster$Student),"")
lastname<-sapply (name,"[",2)
firstname<-sapply(name,"[",1)
roster<-cbind(firstname, lastname,roster[,-1])
roster<-roster[order(lastname,firstname),]
roster
